Merrill McCormick https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Merrill_McCormick 0 Merrill McCormick (February 5, 1892 – August 19, 1953) was an American film actor. He appeared in more than 250 films between 1916 and 1953. McCormick appeared in films like The Last Chance (1926) as Black Bart, The Prisoner of Shark Island, Oh, Susanna!, Heroes of the Alamo as one of the Alamo's defenders, Stagecoach, Dodge City, Man of Conquest, Dick Tracy's G-Men, San Antonio, and Buffalo Bill in Tomahawk Territory. His television appearances included The Cisco Kid, The Adventures of Wild Bill Hickok, and The Gene Autry Show. He was born in Denver, Colorado and died in San Gabriel, California from a heart attack. Merrill_McCormick ( February_5_,_1892 – August_19_,_1953 ) was an_American_film_actor .
